<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Social-Media-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1" alt="Social media bill: Human dignity protection assured — Lawmaker" class="amp-wp-295b586">  Sen. Mohammed Musa (APC- Niger), has urged Nigerians to support the social media bill before the National Assembly because it was aimed at protecting human dignity. Musa said this in a statement on Monday in Abuja. He said the bill, when assented to, would protect human dignity among many other inherent gains. The Senate had on Nov 5, re-introduced the ‘Protection from Internet Falsehood and Manipulations Bill 2019’, to regulate the use of social media in the country. Continue reading Social media bill: Human dignity protection assured — Lawmaker at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard